(97, 'TRACEROUTE', 'In computing, traceroute is a computer network diagnostic tool for displaying the route (path) and measuring transit delays of packets across an Internet Protocol (IP) network. The history of the route is recorded as the round-trip times of the packets received from each successive host (remote node) in the route (path); the sum of the mean times in each hop indicates the total time spent to establish the connection. Traceroute proceeds unless all (three) sent packets are lost more than twice, then the connection is lost and the route cannot be evaluated. Ping, on the other hand, only computes the final round-trip times from the destination point.', 2),
(98, 'COID', '? something to do with DID', 2),
(99, 'TCAM', 'Telecommunications Access Method (TCAM) \r\n\r\nis an access method, in IBM''s OS/360 and successors computer operating systems on IBM System/360 and later, that...\r\n\r\n&quot;provides access to terminals units \r\nwithin a teleprocessing network.&quot;', 2),
(100, 'NAS', 'Network-attached storage (NAS) is a file-level computer data storage server connected to a computer network providing data access to a heterogeneous group of clients. NAS is specialized for serving files either by its hardware, software, or configuration. It is often manufactured as a computer appliance â€“ a purpose-built specialized computer.[nb 1]', 0),
(101, 'GRUNT', ' Grunt is a JavaScript Task Runner. It lets you automate repetitive tasks like minification, compilation, unit testing, linting, etc', 0),
(102, 'BOWER', ' Bower is a front-end package manager. It allows you to simple include, remove, upgrade various packages available for front-end development. You can see various at http://bower.io/search/', 0),
(103, 'ERP', 'ERP Enterprise Resource Planning  ERP, ERM !!!!!resource resource \r\n	product planning, purchase--manufacturing or service delivery--marketing and sales--inventory management--shipping and payment--finance\r\n	ILlustration: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enterprise_resource_planning#/media/File:ERP_Modules.png', 0),
(104, 'ITPM ', 'ITPM -  Information Technology Portfolio Management', 0),
(105, 'EHR', 'An electronic health record (EHR), or electronic medical record (EMR), refers to the systematized collection of patient and population electronically-stored health information in a digital format.[1] These records can be shared across different health care settings. Records are shared through network-connected, enterprise-wide information systems or other information networks and exchanges.', 0),
(106, 'BRMS', 'A BRMS or Business Rule Management System is a software system used to define, deploy, execute, monitor and maintain the variety and complexity of decision logic that is used by operational systems within an organization or enterprise. This logic, also referred to as business rules, includes policies, requirements, and conditional statements that are used to determine the tactical actions that take place in applications and systems.', 0),
(107, 'AG', 'Founded in 1969, Software AG is an enterprise software company with over 10,000 enterprise customers in over 70 countries. ', 0),
(108, 'EMEA', 'EMEA (or EMEIA if India is included) is a shorthand designation meaning Europe, the Middle East and Africa. It is used by institutions and governments, as well as in marketing and business. It is particularly common among North American companies.', 0),
(109, 'GULP', 'Gulp JS is a Javascript based tool which allows you to automates the tasks of your workflow. Automation can literally increase your production. Whether youâ€™re a developer or a designer who creates HTML wireframes now and then, we recommends to dig into that.', 0),
(110, 'IDOC', 'IDoc (category SAP SE)\r\nIDoc, short for Intermediate Document, is a SAP document format for business transaction data transfers. Non SAP-systems can use IDocs as the standard interface  parkseed', 0),
(111, 'SAP R/3 ', 'SAP R/3 (section Technology)\r\nis based on SAP NetWeaver: core components can be implemented in ABAP and in Java and new functional areas are mostly no longer created as part of the  parkseed', 0),
(112, 'MRP', 'process planning (MPP) Material requirements planning (MRP) Manufacturing resource planning (MRP II) Product data management (PDM) Product lifecycle management  parkseed', 0),
(113, 'CRM', 'Customer Relationship Management', 0),
(114, 'SKU', 'SKU may refer to: Stock keeping unit, a unique identifier for each distinct product and service that can be purchased in business Sri Krishnadevaraya parkseed', 0),
(115, 'PCI COMPLIANT', 'Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (redirect from Pci compliant)\r\nEncryption (P2PE) technology, however they are still required to be PCI DSS compliant. Smaller merchants and service providers are not required to explicitly  parkseed', 0),
(116, 'ORM', 'Object-relational mapping (ORM, O/RM, and O/R mapping tool) in computer science is a programming technique for converting data between incompatible type systems in object-oriented programming languages. This creates, in effect, a "virtual object database" that can be used from within the programming language. There are both free and commercial packages available that perform object-relational mapping, although some programmers opt to construct their own ORM tools.  parkseed', 0),
(117, 'AWS', 'AWS  Amazon Web Services', 0),
(118, 'DPE', 'Dynamic provisioning environment (DPE) is a simplified way to explain a complex networked server computing environment where server computing instances or virtual machines (VMs) are provisioned (deployed or instantiated) from a centralized administrative console or client application by the server administrator, network administrator, or any other enabled user. The server administrator or network administrator has the ability to parse out control of the provisioning environment to users or accounts in the network environment (end users, organizational units, network accounts, other administrators). The provisioned servers or VMs can be inside the firewall, outside the firewall, or hosted depending on how the supporting pool of networked server computing resources is defined. From the perspective of the end user/client the requested server is deployed automatically.\r\n\r\n', 0),
(119, 'WEBPACK', 'webpack is a module bundler. Its main purpose is to bundle JavaScript files for usage in a browser, yet it is also capable of transforming, bundling, or packaging just about any resource or asset.', 0),
(120, 'WEB-PACK-DEV-SERVER', 'Serves a webpack app. Updates the browser on changes.', 0),
(121, 'AUTOPREFIXER  USED WITH WEBPACK', 'Parse CSS and add vendor prefixes to rules ', 0),
(122, 'BABEL', 'Babel is a compiler for writing next generation JavaScript. \r\nBabel is a community-driven tool that helps you write the latest version of JavaScript.\r\n\r\nWhen your supported environments don''t support certain features natively, it will help you compile it down to a supported version.', 0),
(123, 'FIREBASE', 'Firebase is a mobile and web application development platform. Firebase is made up of complementary features that developers can mix-and-match to fit their needs. The team is based in San Francisco and Mountain View, California. The company was founded in 2011 by Andrew Lee and James Tamplin.[1] Firebase''s initial product was a realtime database, which provides an API that allows developers to store and sync data across multiple clients. Over time, it has expanded its product line to become a full suite for app development. The company was acquired by Google in October 2014 and a significant number of new features were featured in May 2016 at Google I/O.[6]', 0),
(124, 'HTMLWEBPACKPLUGIN', 'The HtmlWebpackPlugin simplifies creation of HTML files to serve your webpack bundles. This is especially useful for webpack bundles that include a hash in the filename which changes every compilation. You can either let the plugin generate an HTML file for you, supply your own template using lodash templates, or use your own loader.', 0),
(125, 'NODE-SASS', 'Node-sass is a library that provides binding for Node.js to LibSass, the C version of the popular stylesheet preprocessor, Sass.\r\n\r\nIt allows you to natively compile .scss files to css at incredible speed and automatically via a connect middleware.\r\n\r\nFind it on npm: https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-sass', 0),
(126, 'REACTJS', 'React (sometimes styled React.js or ReactJS) is an open-source JavaScript library[2] for building user interfaces.\r\n\r\nIt is maintained by Facebook, Instagram and a community of individual developers and corporations.[3][4][5] According to JavaScript analytics service Libscore, React is currently being used on the websites of Netflix, Imgur, Buffer, Bleacher Report, Feedly, Airbnb, SeatGeek, HelloSign, Walmart, and others.[6]\r\n\r\nReact allows developers to create large web applications that use data which can change over time, without reloading the page. Its main goal is to be fast, simple and scalable. React processes only user interfaces in applications. This corresponds to View in the Model-View-Controller (MVC) template, and can be used in combination with other JavaScript libraries or frameworks in MVC, such as AngularJS.[7]', 0),
(127, 'REDUX', 'Redux is an open-source JavaScript library designed for managing application state. It is primarily used together with React for building user interfaces.', 0),
(128, 'SOURCE-MAP-LOADER', 'Sourcemap Loader\r\nExtracts SourceMaps for source files that as added as `sourceMappingURL` comment.', 0),
(129, 'SOURCE MAPS', 'Have you ever found yourself wishing you could keep your client-side code readable and more importantly debuggable even after you''ve combined and minified it, without impacting performance? Well now you can through the magic of source maps.\r\n\r\nBasically it''s a way to map a combined/minified file back to an unbuilt state. When you build for production, along with minifying and combining your JavaScript files, you generate a source map which holds information about your original files. When you query a certain line and column number in your generated JavaScript you can do a lookup in the source map which returns the original location. Developer tools (currently WebKit nightly builds, Google Chrome, or Firefox 23+) can parse the source map automatically and make it appear as though you''re running unminified and uncombined files.', 0),
(130, 'URL LOADER', 'The url-loader works like the file-loader, but can return a data URL if the file is smaller than a byte limit.\r\n\r\nThe limit can be specified with a query parameter (defaults to no limit).\r\n\r\nIf the file is greater than the limit (in bytes) the file-loader is used and all query parameters are passed to it.', 0),
(131, 'FIREBASE REDIRECT AUTHENTICATION', 'You can let your users authenticate with Firebase using their Google Accounts by integrating Google Sign-In into your app. You can integrate Google Sign-In either by using the Firebase SDK to carry out the sign-in flow, or by carrying out the Google Sign-In flow manually and passing the resulting ID token to Firebase.', 0),
(132, 'CANONICAL LINK', 'A canonical link element is an HTML element that helps webmasters prevent duplicate content issues by specifying the "canonical" or "preferred" version of a web page[1][2] as part of search engine optimization. It is described in RFC 6596, which went live in April 2012.', 0),
(133, 'LANDING PAGE SEO', 'In online marketing, a landing page, sometimes known as a "lead capture page" or a "lander", or a "destination page", is a single web page that appears in response to clicking on a search engine optimized search result or an online advertisement.[1] The landing page will usually display directed sales copy that is a logical extension of the advertisement, search result or link. Landing pages are used for lead generation. The actions that a visitor takes on a landing page is what determines an advertiser''s conversion rate.[2]\r\n\r\nLanding pages are often linked to social media, email campaigns or search engine marketing campaigns in order to enhance the effectiveness of the advertisements. The general goal of a landing page is to convert site visitors into sales or leads. If the goal is to obtain a lead, the landing page will include some method for the visitor to get into contact with the company, usually a phone number, or an inquiry form. If a sale is required, the landing page will usually have a link for the visitor to click, which will then send them to a shopping cart or a checkout area. By analyzing activity generated by the linked URL, marketers can use click-through rates and conversion rate to determine the success of an advertisement', 0),
(134, 'UFOC', ' UFOC (unstyled flash of content) issues', 0),
(135, 'SEO TDM 1', 'Consulting Call 1 of 2 on 5/18/2017\r\nAttendees: Jason Dowdell, Ardalan, Bill, Paul, (Bayan).\r\nTop Issues\r\n1.	Linking to significantly more non-indexable urls than indexable urls resulting in low quality score sitewide and Google crawling hundreds of thousands more pages than necessary each day.\r\n2.	Too many links per page.\r\n3.	Multiple over-optimization signals.\r\nSitewide Issues & Their Causes\r\nâ€¢	Issue: Low Quality URLs\r\no	Non-Canonical urls linked throughout site in several forms.\r\nï‚§	Dynamic category urls versus SEO category urls\r\nï‚§	Filtered dynamic category urls versus SEO category urls\r\n \r\nï‚§	Dynamic Article urls linked as well as SEO versions of urls (Pg 4 of Canonical URLs Report)\r\nï‚§	SEO Article urls canonicalize to a different form of the url\r\n \r\no	Causes\r\n\r\nï‚§	SSL urls are 302 redirecting to the article.aspx pages which canonicalize to a variation of the SEO url with â€œwgâ€ in the file name. These SSL urls are all being linked from the signin.aspx page since itâ€™s on SSL and uses relative links.\r\nï‚§	Left navigation on categories provides crawlable links to Googlebot for all filters even though none of them are indexable.\r\nï‚§	Hand-made merchandising links have not been updated to point to their correct SEO urls.\r\n\r\nEx: On http://www.waysidegardens.com/category.aspx?c=WG_GardenSolutions_S12 these links above the product lists all point to the dynamic url such as http://www.waysidegardens.com/category.aspx?c=AC_1003_27 instead of http://www.waysidegardens.com/butterfly-lovers/c/AC_1003_27/.\r\n\r\n  \r\nï‚§	Some SEO urls are linked with their mixed case version but all canonicals use lowercase versions of urls.\r\n\r\nEx: http://www.waysidegardens.com/Agastache/c/GE_1003_11/ has 3,603 links internally but the canonical tag points to the version that isnâ€™t linked http://www.waysidegardens.com/agastache/c/GE_1003_11/. Top nav links to these mixed case urls.\r\n\r\nEx: http://www.waysidegardens.com/WG-Rose-Supply/c/WG-Rose-Supply/ is linked in top nav but canonicalizes to variation of mixed case url http://www.waysidegardens.com/wg-rose-supply/c/WG-Rose-Supply/. \r\n\r\n\r\nï‚§	Paged links, sort by links and View All links are crawlable & only previous, next & last page links should be.\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Issue: Too many links per page is preventing Google from passing PageRank accurately and in a contextual manner. Site averages 234 links per page. Categories have over 300 links per page.\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Issue: Top nav uses title attributes on all text links which is an over-optimization signal. List the 2nd most important issue here along with what caused it.\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Issue: Links on PLPâ€™s to each product are repeated signaling over-optimization via keyword stuffing of internal anchor text.\r\n\r\nTo Do List\r\n1.	jQuery all rollover links in top nav. Once within a top level tab, the categories within that tab may be crawlable.\r\na.	http://client.seotool.com/tool/kb/architecture/reducing-link-bloat-with-jquery.cfm \r\n2.	jQuery all filtered results in left nav.\r\n3.	jQuery Sort By, Show All pagination links.\r\n4.	jQuery all Email Friend links.\r\n5.	Consolidate multiple links on PLPâ€™s to each PDP into a single link or jQuery the 2nd link.\r\n6.	Remove title attributes from all links sitewide.\r\n7.	Employ absolute links to nonssl pages from the signin.aspx page.\r\n8.	Update Top nav to link to correct case (mixed or lower or combo) url for all categories and subcategories.\r\n9.	Update all hand-merchandized links to point to their canonical version.\r\n10.	Send Jason access to log files for VanDykes from Jan 15 2017 through March 15 2017. These can be filtered for Googlebot.\r\n', 0),
(136, 'SEO TDM 2', 'Soft 404 Footprints for Out of Stock Products\r\nVisible Text Signals on Product Detail Pages \r\nWhen a product is out of stock, the ability to purchase the item will â€œusuallyâ€ be disabled. Meaning, there wonâ€™t be a â€œadd to cartâ€ or â€œbuyâ€ button. Sometimes there will be no product description, images, price information or anything other than a note letting you know itâ€™s no longer available.\r\nTemporarily Out of Stock\r\nâ€¢	â€œOUT OF STOCKâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThis item is currently out of stock and it may or may not be restockedâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œWe''re sorry, but the product that you are searching for is sold out at this time, or is no longer available. For more information please contact customer serviceâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œBe notified when item is in stockâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œManufacturer Out of Stockâ€\r\nâ€¢	Buy | Add to Cart button has been removed.\r\nâ€¢	â€œI apologize if you cannot find this card for sale. I can assure you that it has not been discontinued, it is just out of stock. We are still currently manufacturing this card, but the Top version is produced less than the standard version so stock is very limited. If you have any questions feel free to contact me at cl-jeremy@asus.com.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œWe''re sorry, but * is sold out at this time, or is no longer available.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œWe''re sorry. The list you are trying to view is no longer active.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe product you are trying to view no longer exists.â€\r\nPermanent\r\nâ€¢	â€œDiscontinuedâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThis item is currently out of stock and it may or may not be restockedâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThis item is no longer available.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe product you requested is no longer available.â€\r\nUnknown\r\nâ€¢	No product image available (displays default â€“ no product image image)\r\nâ€¢	No product description\r\nâ€¢	â€œWe are sorry but the sku requested was not found.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œInvalid Product Code specifiedâ€\r\n\r\n\r\nVisible Text on Search Results / Category / Refinement Pages\r\nâ€¢	One or more items with OOS indicators.\r\nâ€¢	One or more items where â€œAdd to Cartâ€ action replaced by  â€œAuto Notifyâ€ or â€œBe Notifiedâ€.\r\nâ€¢	No results found\r\no	May not have anything other than boilerplate header and footer w/o any messaging (RockCreek).\r\no	â€œResults 1-0 of 0â€\r\no	â€œresults 0 of 0â€\r\no	â€œItems 0-0 of 0 totalâ€\r\no	â€œYour search * found 0 resultsâ€\r\no	â€œwe found 0 resultsâ€\r\no	â€œwe have found 0 active itemsâ€\r\no	â€œwe have found 0 itemsâ€\r\no	â€œyour search * did not match any (products|documents)â€\r\no	â€œYour search returns no resultsâ€\r\no	â€œSorry, we were unable to find any matchesâ€\r\no	â€œNo results foundâ€\r\no	(0|No) results returned\r\no	No matches found\r\no	â€œSorry, we were unable to find any results using your search terms. Please change your search terms and try againâ€\r\nâ€¢	Additional modifiers on pages with no results includeâ€¦\r\no	â€œhelpful hintsâ€\r\no	Suggestions\r\nï‚§	â€œdid you meanâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œtry one of these related searchesâ€\r\no	Try\r\nï‚§	â€œUse single wordsâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œCheck your spellingâ€, â€œDouble-check your spelling, try varying the spelling, browse by product category, or explore the suggested items based on your search belowâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œLess specific termâ€, â€œLimit the search to just one or two termsâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œnarrow your selectionâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œtry a different keywordâ€, â€œWe did not understand your input please try a different keywordâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œnarrow your selectionâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œsearch againâ€\r\nï‚§	Be less specific with your search terms. Using more general terms is more likely to lead you to similar or related products.\r\nï‚§	Please change your criteria and search again\r\nï‚§	\r\no	Answers\r\nï‚§	â€œWe are sorry *â€\r\nï‚§	â€œno longer availableâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œare sold outâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œWe''re sorry, there are no videos available that match your requestâ€\r\nï‚§	â€œSorry, we were unable to find any matchesâ€\r\no	â€œshowing results using some of your search termsâ€\r\no	â€œoopsâ€, â€œthere is a problemâ€, â€œwe did not understand your (input|search|request)â€\r\n\r\n\r\nImproperly Handled Errors Causing Soft 404 Message\r\nVisible Text Signals on any Page\r\n404â€™s Returning Status Code 200 - Ok\r\nâ€¢	â€œ404 Not Found Errorâ€, â€œUnexpected Errorâ€, â€œ404 Error - Page Not Foundâ€, â€œFile Not Foundâ€, â€œDirectory Not Foundâ€, â€œHTTP Error 404â€, â€œPost Not Foundâ€, â€œAn Error Has Occurredâ€\r\nâ€¢	In Title: â€œ404 Not Found Errorâ€, â€œPage Not Foundâ€, â€œNo Longer Existsâ€, â€œ404â€, â€œErrorâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œpage that you were looking for no longer existsâ€, â€œFile Not Foundâ€, â€œContent Unavailableâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œWe apologize for the inconvenience. â€œ, â€œapologize for the inconvenienceâ€, â€œif you continue to see this errorâ€, â€œOops! It looks like the page you are trying to reach cannot be found. Please hit the back button on your browser or use any of the links above to navigate to another page on the site.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe post you requested cannot be found or no longer exists. The administrator or moderator may have deleted the post.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œSorry, this auction has been removed from the site.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe page you requested was not found, and we have a fine guess whyâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe content you have requested is no longer available.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe page you are looking for was not foundâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œIf you typed the URL directly, please make sure the spelling is correctâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œIf you clicked on a link to get here, the link is outdatedâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œwhat can you doâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œgo back to the previous pageâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œfollow these links to get you back on trackâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe page you tried to access may be inactive. Or thereâ€™s a chance you typed the address (URL) incorrectlyâ€.\r\nâ€¢	â€œThe page you tried to access does not exist on this serverâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œSorry. Our website is temporarily unavailable. We apologize for any inconvenience. Please call 800.967.6696 to place an order or visit us again later today.â€\r\nâ€¢	â€œWhoops, our badâ€\r\nâ€¢	â€œAccess denied You are not allowed to access that resourceâ€\r\nâ€¢	False Positives:\r\no	â€œfalse , tnp can''t find what they are looking forâ€\r\n404â€™s Returning Status Code 30(1|2) (Permanent | Temporary Redirect)\r\nâ€¢	Redirects to homepage\r\nâ€¢	.NET sites: redirect to â€œ(4xx|5xx).html?aspxerrorpath=/path.aspxâ€\r\no	Redirect to a url with â€œerrorâ€ in the file, path or url parameter\r\nâ€¢	Redirect to a page previously flagged as a soft 404.\r\no	Default / Virtual directory listings that display the contents of a physical folder on the web server.\r\nï‚§	Redirect to same url with trailing slash â€œ/â€ appended that has already been labeled as a Soft 404. \r\nEx: http://www.howardcomputers.com/literature/Howard/current/contracts 301â€™s to http://www.howardcomputers.com/literature/Howard/current/contracts/\r\no	http://www.thegardengates.com/Guy-Wolff-Maryland-Pots-p23570.aspx redirects to http://www.thegardengates.com/PageNotFound.htm?aspxerrorpath=/Guy-Wolff-Maryland-Pots-p23570.aspx\r\n\r\nThin / No Content\r\nâ€¢	Page with no html markup and a single line of text or no visible text at all.\r\no	{success:true}\r\no	â€œPlease enter your email addressâ€\r\no	â€œThis script is locked to another domainâ€\r\no	Login\r\no	The requested information is not available at this time. Please try again later.\r\no	Security check\r\nâ€¢	Page content is 100% identical to other pages on the site\r\no	Contains an additional 404 indicator such as â€œ404â€, â€œerrorâ€, â€œnot foundâ€, â€œsorryâ€ in the title and/or visible text of the page.\r\no	Common causes are includes and popup windows.\r\no	â€œInvalid Product Code specifiedâ€\r\nâ€¢	Nearly identical content with slight variation.\r\no	â€œSorry, the key code (ZWW2571) is invalid or the offer has expired.â€\r\no	â€œPlease verify the key code and the expiration date and try again.â€\r\no	No unique links on page.\r\nâ€¢	Contents of virtual directory listed (server default). These pages will return mime-type of text/html, a matching title and meta-Description, anchor text of â€œ[To Parent Directory]â€ and contain a link for each file in the folder as well as the last-modified date of each file. The footprint below is for Microsoft-IIS/6.0 default configuration\r\no	Title Formula: â€œ[HostName] â€“ [urlPath]â€\r\no	Meta-Description Formula: â€œ[HostName] â€“ [urlPath]â€\r\no	Link to Parent Directory: â€œ[To Parent Directory]â€\r\no	Example of Title, H1 and link to parent directory\r\n <title>www.howardcomputers.com - /literature/Howard/current/co_brands/vmware/</title>\r\n<H1>www.howardcomputers.com - /literature/Howard/current/co_brands/vmware/</H1>\r\n<A HREF="/literature/Howard/current/co_brands/">[To Parent Directory]</A>\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Boilerplate html returned without any additional content.\r\no	http://www.jewelryvortex.com/pg/jsp/help/general/termsconditions.jsp\r\nâ€¢	Bad link indexed by search engine spider causes application to return unpredictable results of little value to search engines.\r\no	No <html></html> tags found.\r\no	No <head></head> section found.\r\nï‚§	No <title></title> found.\r\nï‚§	No <meta name=â€Descriptionâ€ content=â€Blah Blah Blahâ€¦â€ /> found.\r\nï‚§	No <meta name=â€Keywordsâ€ content=â€Blah Blah Blahâ€¦â€ /> found.\r\nï‚§	No <link rel=â€canonicalâ€ source=http://www.seotool.com/ /> found.\r\no	No <body></body> section found.\r\nï‚§	No <H1></H1> headings found.\r\nâ€¢	Sites employing url rewriting (conversion of dynamic urls with ?, &, and = to static urls void of any url parameters) returning improper status codes.\r\nâ€¢	 Sites employing url rewriting (conversion of dynamic urls with ?, &, and = to static urls void of any url parameters) returning improper status codes Visible text limited to small string of text with an apology.\r\nâ€¢	Sitemap page returned\r\no	â€œsite mapâ€ or â€œsitemapâ€\r\no	No unique links are found on this page that have not already been discovered elsewhere on the site.\r\nâ€¢	False Positives:\r\no	â€œIf this is not your catalog then please click hereâ€\r\nï‚§	This page uses an iFrame to pull in contents from an external site but has very little unique text otherwise so a search engine spider doesnâ€™t know the page is valuable / helpful to a real user.\r\nEx: http://www.famous-smoke.com/brand/oliva\r\no	http://www.hayneedle.com/hayneedle_66-2.xml\r\nï‚§	This is supposed to be a sitemap file. I believe it is returning a false positive for 2 reasons. First, the mime type returned is â€œapplication/xmlâ€ and should be â€œtext/xmlâ€ since this is a sitemap file. Secondly, it contains only xml markup and no visible text so it technically has no â€œcontentâ€ that could be added to Googleâ€™s index.\r\n\r\nDynamic URLS Causing Soft 404 Message\r\nURL Components\r\nIncorrect url parameter usage\r\nâ€¢	URL parameters without any values assigned (missing â€œ=â€ sign)\r\no	http://www.affordablescales.com/product_typeind.asp?tpd\r\no	http://www.affordablescales.com/scales_model.asp?scales=768&Soehnle_CERTIFIED_CLASSIC_XL\r\no	http://www.affordablescales.com/scales_model.asp?scales=830&Soehnle_FUTURA\r\nâ€¢	 Multiple urls parameters without any values assigned\r\nâ€¢	Unnecessary / redundant url parameters. Dynamic parameter duplicates content found on url without dynamic parameter. Examples often involve paged results, specifying sort order unnecessarily, indicating 1st page of results instead of leaving the page parameter out, specifying the number of results to display per page unnecessarily (when it is the same as the default number to display), etcâ€¦\r\no	Ex: http://www.expohomes.com/testimonial.asp?page=9 serves same content as http://www.expohomes.com/testimonial.asp As a result, the dynamic parameter adds no value and should actually return a 404.\r\no	http://www.giftbasketsplus.com/?limit=25\r\no	http://www.giftbasketsplus.com/holiday-gift-baskets/wedding-gift-baskets?p=1&page=1 is same as http://www.giftbasketsplus.com/holiday-gift-baskets/wedding-gift-baskets?p=1 and http://www.giftbasketsplus.com/holiday-gift-baskets/wedding-gift-baskets\r\no	http://www.giftbasketsplus.com/holiday-gift-baskets/wedding-gift-baskets?dir=asc&order=position&p=2 is same as http://www.giftbasketsplus.com/holiday-gift-baskets/wedding-gift-baskets?p=2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n', 0),
