(146, 'IIFE', ' Immediately Invoked Function Expression (IIFE). angularjs', 0),
(147, 'UET AND BING', 'Universal Event Tracking (UET) helps customers track their campaign performance with the ability to count unique conversions, associate conversion goals with a single account and track the status of tags and goals. Remarketing works in conjunction with UET and Conversion Tracking to help you reach your business goals.', 0),
(148, 'X FRAME RESPONSE HEADER X-FRAME XFRAME', 'X Frame Response header:\r\n\r\nThis is an update we''re doing for all of our clients. Previously the X-frame options were at the IIS level. This was good for site security; having X-Frame options specified to prevent people from clickjacking the site. However, it was not good when specific parties needed to gain access. For example, if a 3rd party search needed access (like SLI). We''ve moved the X-frame options to the integration level (within controls/form handlers) so we still have the X-frames in place to prevent site injections, but it allows the client a way to more easily give specific parties access.\r\n\r\nYou can see more info here:\r\nhttps://www.owasp.org/index.php/Clickjacking_Defense_Cheat_Sheet\r\n\r\nFrom that link:\r\n"The X-Frame-Options HTTP response header can be used to indicate whether or not a browser should be allowed to render a page in a <frame> or <iframe>. Sites can use this to avoid Clickjacking attacks, by ensuring that their content is not embedded into other sites. Set the X-Frame-Options header for all responses containing HTML content. The possible values are "DENY", "SAMEORIGIN", or "ALLOW-FROM uri""\r\n', 0),
