(342, 'inmotion support email', 'Dear frederick forte,\r\n\r\nIt was a pleasure speaking with you today. Per our conversation, I''m providing you with information from our Support Center to help you get started with using your new account. Once your account has been provisioned, you will receive your Welcome E-mail with a link to set your password and begin using your account.\r\n\r\n\r\nSupport Center\r\nBackups: Create a Full cPanel Backup\r\n\r\nCreating Email Accounts\r\n\r\nGetting Started Guide: Email\r\n\r\nGetting Started Guide: New Customers\r\n\r\nInstall Wordpress\r\n\r\nPointing to Our Nameservers\r\n\r\nSubmitting and Checking on the Status of Tickets\r\n\r\nTransfer Domain Name\r\n\r\nWebsite Transfer Request\r\n\r\nWordpress 101\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn addition to the information I''ve provided, our Support Center offers a wealth of information on a variety of topics related to using our service. If you require additional assistance, our Support department can be reached via chat, email or phone 24/7. Thanks for choosing InMotion Hosting!\r\n\r\nSincerely, \r\n\r\nYvonne H. \r\nInMotion Hosting \r\n888-321-HOST(4678) \r\nhttp://www.inmotionhosting.com \r\nhttp://www.inmotionhosting.com/support', '', 3),
(343, 'inmotion reciept', 'Please save this receipt for your records.\r\n\r\nfrederick forte\r\n3230 Old Milton Rd\r\nClinton South Carolina, 29325\r\nReceipt: IMH-414-1209186-1\r\nDate: 2017-05-31\r\n\r\nTotal Charge: $317.68\r\n\r\nTerm	Subscription	Renewal	Price\r\n1 year	R-1000S (forteworks.com)	2018-05-31	$268.68\r\n0 	2 Hours - Managed Hosting (forteworks.com)	2018-05-31	$49.00\r\nTotal Charge: $317.68\r\nBilled to: 4551\r\nTotal Due: $0.00\r\nIn order to ensure your site remains online, our products are set to "Auto Renew," and your subscription will automatically renew for successive periods until cancellation. Upon renewal, you authorize InMotion Hosting, Inc to charge the standard subscription amount to the payment method provided by you, for as long as you choose to remain a subscriber. You can setup email reminders about your subscription by logging into your Account Management Panel (AMP)\r\n\r\nThank you for your business.\r\n\r\n888-321-HOST (4678) Available 24/7\r\nhttp://www.inmotionhosting.com\r\nhttp://www.inmotionhosting.com/support\r\n', '', 3),
(344, 'inmotion managed hosting support', 'Hello frederick, \r\n\r\nThank you for your recent purchase of Launch Assist, which includes 2 hours of Managed Hosting support! The Managed Hosting team is composed of experienced system administrators who are here to help you get started with your new account. \r\n\r\nWe can help you get started with any website transfers you may require or give you advice regarding your new reseller account. \r\n\r\nWe would like to start by asking about the goals you would like to achieve with your new reseller account. Please let us know what your needs are, whether it be website transfers, troubleshooting, or anything else. We would like to know so that we can better assist you. \r\n\r\nThere are two primary ways to get in touch with the Managed Hosting team: \r\n\r\n1) Via Telephone \r\n\r\n- Our direct phone number is 757-416-6581. When you dial this number, you will immediately receive the Managed Hosting welcome message and be routed to one of our technicians within the department. \r\n\r\n- Alternatively, you can reach us at our toll-free number at 1-888-321-4678 and press the hidden option of 7 at the main menu. You will receive the Managed Hosting welcome message and be routed to an available technician. \r\n\r\n2) E-Mail / Ticket \r\n\r\n- You can submit an e-mail any time at the following e-mail address or simply reply to this email or email advanced@inmotionhosting.com \r\n\r\nManaged Hosting Operating Hours: \r\n\r\n9AM - 9PM Eastern, Monday through Friday \r\n\r\n\r\nFrequently asked questions: \r\n\r\nQ:"What if I need support outside of your operating hours?" \r\n\r\nA: Our regular support department is always available to assist you 24 hours a day, seven days a week at 1-888-321-4678, option 2. \r\n\r\nQ: "What can I expect as a member of this service?" \r\n\r\nA: The Managed Hosting team can be considered as your personal Linux systems administration team. We are here to provide advice of issues before they become issues, plan for the growth of your business''s site, and provide assistance when emergencies happen. \r\n\r\nQ: "What is the best way to contact the Managed Hosting team?" \r\n\r\nA: The best way to be in contact with us is through a blend of phone contact and support tickets. To get the most detail and understand of your needs as best as we can, we would like to speak to you over the phone when you require immediate assistance. Once we understand what your needs are, we will open a ticket to provide tracking of the task and begin working to accomplish it. If there is too much information to cover, you may want to submit a support ticket. You can always call us or request a call for any clarification in your request. \r\n\r\nQ: "How can I maximize my Managed Hosting time?" \r\n\r\nA: When making requests, support tickets are usually the best way to provide information and get your request started. Phone calls are great for clarifying issues quickly. It is best to balance contact between phone calls and support tickets accordingly. Use our regular support department, which is always included, will save your Managed Hosting time for the tasks which are outside the scope of traditional support or require a higher priority of service. \r\n\r\n\r\nIf at any time you are unhappy with the service you are receiving, have questions, or have any suggestions, please feel free to open a ticket to advanced@inmotionhosting.com with "ATTN: MANAGER" in the subject line. We are very open to feedback and want to know if your experience could be better and how we can accurately meet your needs. \r\n\r\nOnce again, thank you for your recent purchase and we welcome you to Managed Hosting. We look forward to working with you and are excited to help you meet your goals. \r\n\r\n\r\nBest Regards, \r\n\r\nThe Managed Hosting Team \r\nInMotion Hosting, Inc. \r\n888-321-4678, option 7 \r\n757-416-6581 \r\nManaged Hosting Hours: Mon-Fri 9AM-9PM ET \r\n\r\nTraditional Support (888-321-4678, option 2) is available 24/7 \r\n\r\nFor answers to commonly asked questions, visit: \r\nhttp://www.inmotionhosting.com/support ', '', 3),
(345, 'kindred', '* CS, Engineering, Math, etc. or equivalent work experience in the technical arena \r\n* 5+ years in a full-time software developer role, with a progressive increase in responsibility and title \r\n* Solid, powerful, and confident written and verbal communication skills - the ability to communicate complex thoughts and ideas in a clear and concise manner \r\n* Experience with modern source control systems (git, Subversion, etc.) \r\n* Skills working directly with end users \r\n* Experience in accurately estimating timelines and work efforts, and a history of hitting your estimates \r\n* History of documenting your designs and development for current/future reviews \r\n* Experience enhancing and supporting large-scale, mission-critical applications \r\n* Ability to multi-task, working on multiple projects and/or provide ongoing enhancements and support to existing applications \r\n* Windows, Unix/AIX, C#.NET, ADO.NET, SQL Server, Perl, C++, HTML, JavaScript, b-tree index, XML/XSLT, Java, Python, mobile platforms, and several others \r\n* Have experience with application design techniques, user interface design, and development of design documents \r\n* Be an analytical thinker, excited about tackling new problems and learning new technologies \r\n* Have experience working directly with stakeholders to translate workflows and business needs to UX processes and UI design for web based, client based and mobile applications \r\n* Have experience creating mockups from wireframe stage to final production ready design assets for both web and IOS\r\n* Have experience with creation of page templates, CSS styles sheets, presentation layer code, content and style guides \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWindows\r\nUnix/AIX : AIX is an enterprise-class UNIX operating system (OS) for the POWER processor architecture found in IBM Power Systems. \r\nC#.NET   : C# is a type-safe,  object-oriented language\r\nADO.NET  : 		ADO.NET is a data access technology from the Microsoft .NET Fr