extracts the nav bar\r\nin layout.blade.php\r\n@include(''partials.nav''); // or @include(''layouts.nav'');\r\nnow...resources/views/layout/nav.blade.php\r\npastes the nav bar code in here\r\n\r\n@include(''layouts.footer'')\r\n//does same thing for the footer.\r\n\r\nat this point layout.blade.php looks kind of like this...\r\n</div>\r\n@include(''layouts.nav'')\r\n\r\n<div class="container">\r\n	@yield(''content'')\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n@include(''layouts.footer'')\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n\r\n...now he registers another ROUTE  for ...\r\nresources/views/posts/show.blade.php\r\n\r\nRoute::get(''/posts/{post}'',''PostsController@show'');\r\n\r\n...now for conventions sake he renames layout.blade.php to master.blade.php\r\n...and then references it as @extends(''layouts.master'')\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n6)------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 3),
