(479, 'SEO Best Practices from TDM', 'SEO Best Practices ï‚· Titles and Meta Descriptions should be updated so they are all unique and within the Best Practice guidelines. o Titles Best Practices o No more than ~58 characters. o Do not duplicate a keyword. o Does not target the same keyword phrase as another page. o Is enticing for the users to click, reads well. o No misspellings. o Donâ€™t use special characters such as â€œ, â€œ, @, #, %, *, (, ), etc. ï‚· Meta Description Best Practices o More than 50 characters, but no more than 165 characters. o Do not duplicate a keyword. o Is unique from other pages. o Is enticing for the users, it should encourage them to click by giving them a call to action or value add such as Free Shipping, Best Price, etc. o No misspellings. o Donâ€™t use special characters such as â€œ, â€œ, @, #, %, *, (, ), etc. ï‚· Headings o There should only be a single unique H1 tag that complements (not duplicates) the Title tag. o Headings should be like an outline of a paper, there should be one primary Heading (H1) and all the others (H2+) should support it. o Headings should not be in navigational or static elements.  Do not have multiple uses of the keyword in the H1. ï‚· On-page content o Ideally each page should have 350+ words of unlinked content with 2 â€“ 3 occurrences of the targeted keyword phrase. o Use the target phrase in the first sentence. o No misspellings. o Keep the user in mind. o Keep any links within content to just a few, if needed. ', '', 3),
