(531, 'screaming frog seo and ada', 'Screaming Frog:\r\nDOWNLOAD: https://www.screamingfrog.co.uk/seo-spider/\r\n$100 version allows you to crawl more than 500 pages(needed)\r\n\r\nUsage Tutorials:\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZUsJDnpxsVE\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dG9JK8W32Ss\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zHY7Gbr2c1o\r\nADA Compliance Info:\r\nhttps://www.ada.gov/pcatoolkit/chap5toolkit.htm\r\nhttps://www.techrepublic.com/blog/web-designer/creating-an-ada-compliant-website/\r\nADA Checklist:\r\nEvery image, video file, audio file, plug-in, etc. has an alt tag\r\nComplex graphics are accompanied by detailed text descriptions\r\nThe alt descriptions describe the purpose of the objects\r\nIf an image is also used as a link, make sure the alt tag describes the graphic and the link destination\r\nDecorative graphics with no other function have empty alt descriptions (alt= "")\r\nAdd captions to videos\r\nAdd audio descriptions\r\nCreate text transcript\r\nCreate a link to the video rather than embedding it into web pages\r\nAdd a link to the media player download\r\nAdd an additional link to the text transcript\r\nThe page should provide alternative links to the Image Map\r\nThe <area> tags must contain an alt attribute\r\nData tables have the column and row headers appropriately identified (using the <th> tag)\r\nTables used strictly for layout purposes do NOT have header rows or columns\r\nTable cells are associated with the appropriate headers (e.g. with the id, headers, scope and/or axis HTML attributes)\r\nMake sure the page does not contain repeatedly flashing images\r\nCheck to make sure the page does not contain a strobe effect\r\nA link is provided to a disability-accessible page where the plug-in can be downloaded\r\nAll Java applets, scripts and plug-ins (including Acrobat PDF files and PowerPoint files, etc.) and the content within them are accessible to assistive technologies, or else an alternative means of accessing equivalent content is provided\r\nWhen form controls are text input fields use the LABEL element\r\nWhen text is not available use the title attribute\r\nInclude any special instructions within field labels\r\nMake sure that form fields are in a logical tab order\r\nInclude a â€˜Skip Navigation'' button to help those using text readers\r\n\r\n\r\nADA Compliance :\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FFHvzVsnH1I\r\n\r\n1. what is the degree of risk\r\n2. get attorney\r\n3. download www.w3.org/WCAG/\r\n4. REad the guidelines\r\n5. all browsers\r\n6. need iphone and android\r\n7. screen readers\r\n8. Accessibility Extensions\r\n9. Write a policy for procedures(very important to have a record of)\r\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_Content_Accessibility_Guidelines\r\n\r\nWCAG 1.0 consist of 14 guidelinesâ€”each of which describes a general principle of accessible design. Each guideline covers a basic theme of web accessibility and is associated with one or more checkpoints that describes how to apply that guideline to particular webpage features.\r\nGuideline 1: Provide equivalent alternatives to auditory and visual content\r\nGuideline 2: Donâ€™t rely on colour alone\r\nGuideline 3: Use markup and style sheets, and do so properly\r\nGuideline 4: Clarify natural language usage\r\nGuideline 5: Create tables that transform gracefully\r\nGuideline 6: Ensure that pages featuring new technologies transform gracefully\r\nGuideline 7: Ensure user control of time sensitive content changes\r\nGuideline 8: Ensure direct accessibility of embedded user interfaces\r\nGuideline 9: Design for device independence\r\nGuideline 10: User interim solutions\r\nGuideline 11: Use W3C technologies and guidelines\r\nGuideline 12: Provide context and orientation information\r\nGuideline 13: Provide clear navigation mechanisms\r\nGuideline 14: Ensure that documents are clear and simple\r\n\r\n///////////////   SEO ////////////////////////////////////////////////\r\n\r\nfind broken links offer alternative to your page create organic links\r\n\r\nsorting by title\r\n    no duplicates or extra garbage\r\nno duplicate uRLS\r\n\r\nMeta Description\r\n  length 150\r\n\r\nH1 no duplicates\r\nStatus no 404s\r\nword count too few words is not good( maybe merge with another)\r\nResponse Time\r\n\r\n???????????\r\nHow to check Authority?\r\n\r\nwhat stratedgies?\r\n========================================================\r\nHow to increase RANK\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xI1SicZRve0\r\nGA > Audience > Acquisition > SEO > Queries\r\nadvanced filter > for position of 10\r\nfind phrases that we rank just higher than 10 to improve them...\r\nfind a phrase ...take it to google search to confirm the rank...\r\ncheck that you don''t interefere with other similar phrases...\r\n6 days Later\r\nGoogle search for phrases\r\nclicks the world icon\r\nsuccesfully moved link from page two to page one\r\nTurbo SEO\r\n\r\n-----------------------------------------------\r\nBrian Dean of\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lyiikzjg9a0\r\nnew ranking factor\r\nHigh Quality Backlinks\r\nBACKLINKS corner stone of ranking...\r\n\r\nto be best site for keyword:\r\n1)\r\nBucket Brigade...\r\nwords that keep your readers..\r\n\r\nput one at any point where user might get bored of reading...\r\n2) Benefit Driven Sub-Headings\r\ngrab attention ...include benefit..ie. Improve by 100%!\r\nyou have 2 seconds......\r\n\r\n3) APP formula\r\nAgree, Promise, and Preview\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B9x3IkU8eaw\r\n\r\n\r\n//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\r\n\r\n', '', 3),
(532, 'opencart add jquery or javascript', '1.Download jquery-2.1.2.min.js from here:\r\nhttps://code.jquery.com/jquery/\r\n\r\n2.Save it locally as: jquery-2.1.2.min.js\r\n\r\n3. Upload it to your Server into the following Subdirectory:\r\n/cart/admin/view/javascript/jquery/ \r\n\r\n4. NOW, either, a LINK, as shown below, to your ADMIN javascript/jquery/ Sub is already defined in some Extension VqMod, or OcMod, to be ADDED to your /cart/admin/view/template/common/header.tpl, and looking like:\r\n\r\n<script type="text/javascript" src="view/javascript/jquery/jquery-2.1.2.min.js"></script>\r\n\r\nor then, you would have to add such a line into your ADMIN header.tpl, where the other Script-Links are shown, to make it work. ( wich would mean, that you bought a very cheap Mod ;) )\r\n\r\nIn ANY CASE, just make sure, such a LINK directs to the PLACE, where the JS File really exists, on your Server!', '', 3),
