(653, 'wordpress security measures', '\r\nWordpress Security Optimizations\r\n\r\n1) Disable File Editing\r\n  	Place this code in the wp-config.php  \r\n  	<code>\r\n	// Disallow file edit\r\n	define( ''DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT'', true );\r\n	</code>\r\n\r\n2) Disable PHP File Execution by directory in 2 locations.\r\n	A) /wp-content/uploads/ folder.  \r\n	B) /wp-includes/ folder.\r\n\r\n	Add individual .htaccess to each directory with this snippet\r\n	<code>\r\n		<Files *.php>\r\n		deny from all\r\n		</Files>\r\n	</code>\r\n	REFERENCE: http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-disable-php-execution-in-certain-wordpress-directories/\r\n\r\n3) change database prefix\r\n	PLUGIN: Change Table Prefix\r\n			https://wordpress.org/plugins/change-table-prefix/\r\n\r\n4) Disable Directory Indexing and Browsing\r\n	Add this line at the bottom of the  .htaccess\r\n	<code>\r\n	Options -Indexes\r\n	</code>\r\n	REFERENCE: http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/disable-directory-browsing-wordpress/\r\n\r\n5) Logout Idle Users automatically\r\n	Plugin: Idle User Logout\r\n		https://wordpress.org/plugins/idle-user-logout/#screenshots\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n7) XML-RPC\r\n	in the .htaccess  \r\n	<code>\r\n		# Block WordPress xmlrpc.php requests\r\n		<Files xmlrpc.php>\r\n		order deny,allow\r\n		deny from all\r\n		allow from 123.123.123.123\r\n		</Files>\r\n	</code>\r\n	REFERENCE: http://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-disable-xml-rpc-in-wordpress/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nPAID services and Additional Measures\r\n-------------------------------------\r\nWAF (Web Application Firewall)\r\n	Plugin: \r\n		Sucuri \r\n			$200 a year\r\n	REFERENCE: https://sucuri.net/\r\n\r\n\r\nExtra measures:\r\nA) Add Security Questions to Login\r\n	Plugin: WP Security Questions\r\n 		https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-security-questions/\r\n', '', 3),
