(657, 'thinkful tutorial tips', 'Strategy For Problem Solving:\r\n\r\nThe following is one of the examples they ask you to do in the ''javascript classroom'' repl.it\r\nmentioned in the ''tech eval'' study guide.\r\nThe comments I added are the steps to take for each function problem.\r\nWhat goes IN and what goes OUT, it might sound simple but it''s crucial to get right.\r\nIf you don''t know how to do it RESEARH: \r\nmake a google search that contains just the key words about what you are trying to do.\r\n-e.g. "javascript object remove property" \r\nand you might want to add another keyword like " stackoverflow "\r\n\r\nWhat language?       javascript\r\nWhat are we working with ?      object , array, other...\r\nWhat are we trying to do?       remove a property\r\nI put the ''RESULT'' part in for you just to see what search came up for me in this circumstance.\r\nand last the EXAMPLE: delete myObject[prop]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nfunction removeProperty(obj, key) {\r\n  // your code here\r\n  \r\n  //IN: obj and key\r\n  //OUT: nothing\r\n  //RESEARCH: javascript object remove property\r\n  //RESULT:https://stackoverflow.com/questions/208105/how-do-i-remove-a-property-from-a-javascript-object\r\n  //EXAMPLE: delete myObject[prop];\r\n  \r\n  delete obj[key];\r\n  \r\n}\r\n\r\nSo in summary.\r\n\r\nfunction whatever(a,b){\r\n//IN:\r\n//OUT:\r\n//RESEARCH:\r\n//EXAMPLE:\r\n\r\n//your code....\r\n\r\n// return OUT if required.\r\n}\r\n\r\nThe next thing I would  do is ...line up all my ''go to'' research sites...\r\n\r\nJS:         https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/jsref_obj_array.asp\r\nCSS:      https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_examples.asp\r\nHTML:   https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_examples.asp\r\n(tack on others as you go...)\r\n\r\nuse these or substitute other site you like \r\n\r\n ', '', 3),
