(659, 'upwork proposal 1', 'https://www.upwork.com/o/jobs/browse/?q=php%20javascript%20website%20development&sort=renew_time_int%2Bdesc&user_location_match=1\r\nNeed UX designer to help polish up our wordpress website.\r\nWeb & Mobile Design  Posted 17 hours ago\r\nWe are a non-profit company that provides lesson plans to elementary teachers and parents.  We are looking for a designer to help our website stand out. We currently use the Avada theme and do not want to change themes we just need someone to make some tweeks and "sharpen" our current theme.  Minor tweaks to category pages, product pages, etc. \r\n\r\nOngoing work for the right candidate.\r\n\r\nPlease send samples of previous work.\r\n\r\nOnly freelancers located in the U.S. may apply. \r\n\r\nOngoing project: WordPress expert, Website Designer, HTML5 developer\r\nProject Type: Ongoing project\r\nProject Stage: Fully Specified\r\nYou will be asked to answer the following questions when submitting a proposal:\r\n\r\nWhat questions do you have for this project?\r\nWhat challenging part of this job are you most experienced in?\r\n------------------------------\r\nA Basic Project Proposal\r\nFirst of all, I like the fact that you are a non profit educational website.\r\nI see that you want to customize the Wordpress Avada theme.\r\n1) Here are the skills needed...\r\n    First you need to know php, javascript, html, and css. Then you have to understand how wordpress themes and plugins work and relate to each other. Then you have to learn how ''Avada'' codes their themes. Is it straight php or is it object oriented php, etc, etc. Then you have to know how to integrate animations or other non-typical website features into the wordpress eco-system.\r\n\r\n2) Does this outline explain your project  and if so here are the steps to complete it.\r\nYour outline of the project does not give much detail in terms of what kind of features and changes you''d like to make. So in some respects there might already be a pre-made plugin that does what you want. \r\n3) Here''s the reasons for the time and costs.\r\nI would charge $25 an hour just because that''s my regular freelance rate and because I don''t know exactly what the scope of work is.\r\n4) Here are examples of similar projects I have already completed.\r\nI  currently have a full time job working for a company that is transforming all of their subsidiary sites into wordpress platform so I''m actively working in the wordpress eco-system.\r\nI''ve created my own web hosting and design business and use wordpress theme for the front end...https://www.sprite-pilot.com  and here is a basic example of a site I created for me and my wife to teach music and computer programming lessons. http://www.forteworks.com/music\r\n', '', 3),
