(680, 'Amazon AWS S3 images bucket ', '    https://www.joe0.com/2017/03/13/how-to-move-wordpress-images-to-amazon-s3-free-solution/\r\n\r\n    Steps:\r\n    0) create a S3 Bucket on Amazon to hold the images\r\n    1) install AWS plugin\r\n    2) install WP Offload S3 lite\r\n    3) install ''Regenerate thumbnails'' plugin\r\n    4) Amazon Key and secret  \r\n      Admin Menu > AWS > Access Keys\r\n    5) select pre-existing Bucket \r\n      Admin Menu > S3 and Cloudfront > \r\n        also Select ''Advanced Options'' \r\n        [''cloudfront or custom domain'':''off'',\r\n        ''Path'':''On'',\r\n        ''Year/Month'': ''On'',\r\n        ''Force HTTPS'':''off'',\r\n        ''Remove Files from Server'':''ON'',\r\n        ''Object versioning'': ''ON''\r\n        ]\r\n    6) To move ''Existing Images'' as well, run the Regenerate thumbnails plugin. ', '', 3),
(681, 'deploy from VSTS to AWS continuous integration', '\r\nGuys,\r\nBelow is a study/research outline of how we can deploy our websites from VSTS to AWS.\r\n-bayon\r\n\r\nVSTS  Continuous Integration and Delivery\r\nhttps://www.visualstudio.com/team-services/continuous-integration/\r\n\r\n        VSTS Build and release\r\n        https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/vsts/build-release/?view=vsts\r\n\r\n            5 Minute Quick Start ( Docker )\r\n            https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/vsts/build-release/apps/containers/build?view=vsts&tabs=web\r\n\r\n                PREREQUISITES:\r\n                Build you Node.js app with Gulp\r\n                https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/vsts/build-release/apps/nodejs/build-gulp?view=vsts&tabs=gitvsts%2Cweb%2Cdeploy-windows\r\n\r\n                    Prerequistes:\r\n                    vsts account\r\n                    configured a build agent\r\n                    https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/vsts/build-release/actions/agents/v2-windows?view=vsts\r\n\r\n                    Get the sample code- https://github.com/adventworks/nodejs-sample\r\n                    Deploy your App : build and push docker image ...( their link was to an azure related tutorial)\r\n\r\n                    Define a CI build process for your Git repo\r\n                    https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/vsts/build-release/actions/ci-build-git?view=vsts\r\n\r\n                    * at this point app is built and ready to deploy I think\r\n\r\n\r\n                        AWS AWS Tools for Visual Studio\r\n                        https://aws.amazon.com/vsts/\r\n\r\n\r\n                                    AWS AWS CodeDeploy\r\n                                    https://aws.amazon.com/codedeploy/\r\n                                    "integrate with your existing software release process or continuous delivery toolchain"\r\n\r\n                                    AWS App Spec\r\n                                    https://docs.aws.amazon.com/codedeploy/latest/userguide/application-specification-files.html\r\n\r\n                                    AWS CodePipeline\r\n                                    https://aws.amazon.com/codepipeline/\r\n\r\n                                    \r\n                                    connect vsts build to aws codepipeline \r\n\r\n\r\n                                    AWS CodeDeploy with VSTS services\r\n                                    https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/developer/deploying-net-web-applications-using-aws-codedeploy-with-visual-studio-team-services/\r\n\r\nBayon Forte\r\nWeb Developer\r\nASI Design Software | Louisville\r\nP:  (877) GET ASI 1\r\n\r\nweb | map\r\n\r\n       \r\n \r\n\r\nCONFIDENTIALITY STATEMENT: This email transmission is intended only for the use of the individual or entity named above and may contain information that is confidential, privileged, and exempt from disclosure under applicable law. If you are not the intended recipient, you are hereby notified that any disclosure, copying, distribution, or use of any of the information contained in this transmission is strictly prohibited. If you have received this transmission in error, please immediately notify me by email at the above address. \r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 3),
(682, 'aws create vps', '\r\ncreate VPS on AWS\r\ngoto EC2 Panel\r\nlaunch instance\r\nselect ami amazon machine\r\nchoose t2.micro\r\nclick review&launch\r\naccept defaults\r\nclick launch\r\nchoose key pair\r\n    IF NEEDED:\r\n        create key pair\r\n        store key pair\r\nclick launch instance\r\nclick view instances\r\nwait until ''state'' == ''running''\r\ncopy Public IP Address\r\nconnect to instance\r\nopen gitbash\r\n~ ssh -i ''c:\\Users\\yourname\\.ssh\\mykeypair.pem'' ec2-user@{IP_ADDRESS}\r\ntype yes\r\nCONNECTED\r\n\r\nto Terminate:\r\ngoto ec2 Panel\r\nselect box next to your instance\r\nclick Terminate\r\nselect yes \r\nTERMINATED.', '', 3),
