(271, 'Just found out how to enable HTML5 correct mime type for IIS: could be usefull for those with a hosted app on an IIS and wondering how to get it to work.\r\n(someone told me that GoMummy and others use IIS)\r\nCopy code\r\n<!DOCTYPE HTML>\r\n<html manifest="manifest.appcache">\r\n \r\nweb.config in the directory containing the app\r\nCopy code\r\n<configuration>\r\n <system.web>\r\n  <httpHandlers>\r\n   <add verb="GET,HEAD" path="*.appcache"        type="System.Web.StaticFileHandler" />\r\n  </httpHandlers>\r\n </system.web>\r\n <system.webServer>\r\n  <staticContent>\r\n   <mimeMap fileExtension=".appcache"      mimeType="text/cache-manifest" />\r\n  </staticContent>\r\n </system.webServer>\r\n</configuration>', 'app cache on IIS', 'html5'),
