(576, 'The JavaScript method toString() converts an array to a string of (comma separated) array values.\r\nThe join() method also joins all array elements into a string.\r\nThe pop() method removes the last element from an array:\r\nThe push() method adds a new element to an array (at the end):\r\nThe shift() method removes the first array element and "shifts" all other elements to a lower index.\r\nThe unshift() method adds a new element to an array (at the beginning), and "unshifts" older elements:\r\nThe splice() method can be used to add new items to an array: //fruits.splice(position, number of elements, "val1", "val2");\r\nfruits.splice(0, 1);        // Removes the first element of fruits\r\nThe sort() method sorts an array alphabetically:\r\nThe reverse() method reverses the elements in an array.\r\nNumeric Sort:\r\nvar points = [40, 100, 1, 5, 25, 10];\r\npoints.sort(function(a, b){return a-b}); //ascending // lowest number at 0\r\npoints.sort(function(a, b){return b-a}); //descending //highest numeber at 0\r\nThe concat() method creates a new array by concatenating two arrays:\r\nThe slice() method slices out a piece of an array into a new array.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'ARRAY METHODS:', 'javascript'),
