(370, 78, 'The purpose of this document is to define the requirements of the Professional Services department related to reporting their time in the Timesheet section of MaxxPoint. \r\n\r\nTheir requirement is for projects with the status of â€œClosedâ€ or â€œCancelledâ€ to not be presented to them in the Project Dropdowns in the â€œAdd Task to Timesheetâ€ section of the application. The attached screen shot illustrates a current project drop down list for Joe Welch. He reports that nearly all of the listed projects are closed. \r\n\r\nNo change to the functionality of the system is required. The only requested change is to list only active projects in the Project drop down menu. \r\n\r\nThe status of the projects is listed on the â€œProjectsâ€ page within MaxxPoint. Please see the following link and attached screen shot: https://maxxpoint.smoothstone.com/boss/prof-serv_projects \r\n\r\nThe available options for â€œStatusâ€ are: \r\n\r\nÂ· Cancelled \r\n\r\nÂ· Closed \r\n\r\nÂ· Not Started \r\n\r\nÂ· Open \r\n\r\nÂ· Paused \r\n\r\nThe â€œProjectâ€ Drop Down menu on the â€œAdd Task to Timesheetâ€ page should only be populated with projects with a status of â€œNot Started,â€ â€œOpenâ€ or â€œPausedâ€. Projects with a status of â€œCancelledâ€ or â€œClosedâ€ should not have time charged to them and should not be listed in the Drop Down menu. '),
