(414, 90, 'See attached requirements document and mockup in Excel.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this document is to define the requirements of the Solution Management Department to add functionality to ITC to calculate applicable early termination penalties for customers terminating billing services. \r\n\r\nThe users request an interface where they will input:\r\n\r\nÂ·         Client Name (From drop down menu)\r\n\r\nÂ·         Location (From drop down menu)\r\n\r\no   Can be a single location or multiple up to the complete list of sites for a customer\r\n\r\nÂ·         Contract Term (in years)\r\n\r\nÂ·         CTP % per contract\r\n\r\nÂ·         CTP as of date (effective date of cancellation\r\n\r\nUpon entering this information, the system should populate a report/screen with:\r\n\r\nÂ·         Location Address (Each site should have its own section on the report/screen)\r\n\r\nÂ·         All the billing services actively billing on the invoice for all applicable sites\r\n\r\nÂ·         Billable Date (This the Access Billable or Voice Billable date from the Billing Details by Location screen in ITC\r\n\r\nÂ·         Remaining Term (The calculated difference  between the effective CTP date and the end of the contract term)\r\n\r\nÂ·         MRC (per Billing Service from the invoice)\r\n\r\nÂ·         Total CTP (per Billing Service) calculated with the Remaining Term, MRC and CTP %\r\n\r\nÂ·         Subtotal by Location\r\n\r\nÂ·         Grand Total  for all applicable Locations\r\n\r\nÂ·         Summary for all sites\r\n\r\nAttached is a mockup of the report in Excel showing the applicable formulas.  This spreadsheet has been in use by Solution Management for this purpose.   It is very time consuming to create this manually.  This is the reason behind this feature request.\r\n\r\nBelow is a screen shot of the mockup for a single site along with the summary for all sites.\r\n\r\nThe fields highlighted in yellow show the fields the user must enter.  The table beneath displays the look up or calculated results.  The sub-total is visible in the lower right corner of the screen shot.\r\n\r\nA summary of all the sites should be displayed on the report/screen\r\n\r\n\r\nThe report/screen should be exportable to be sent to a customer by Solution Management for communication of fees.\r\n\r\nThe users request the capability to run this report on an ad hoc basis as well as having a link from the Cancel Quote screen (Quote Management) to this function while completing a Cancel SA.');
